    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="nar.02685.001.jpg" type="recto"/>
           
            <ab>Dec. 26, 1871.</ab>
            <note type="editorial">The annotation "I 197" appearing below the dateline in this letter is not in Whitman's hand.</note>
            <ab>Hon. E. G. Bradford,</ab>
            <ab>U.S. District Judge,</ab>
            <ab>Wilmington, Del.</ab>
            <ab>Sir:</ab>
            <ab>I am directed by the Attorney General to acknowledge the receipt of your letter transmitting your oath of office, and to inform you that you should also take (and transmit a copy thereof) the oath prescribed by the Act of July 2d, 1862, (12th U.S. Stats. p. 502.)</ab>
            <ab>Very respectfully,</ab>
            <ab>A. J. Falls,</ab>
            <ab>Chief Clerk.</ab>
            <note type="authorial" place="right">I 197</note>
            <note type="authorial" place="left">Oath &amp;c.</note>
        </body>
